# Trivy ignore file — suppress known false positives.
# Format: <AVD-ID or rule ID> [expiry-date] [reason]
#
# Full list of AVD IDs: https://avd.aquasec.com/misconfig/aws/
# Find the ID for a finding from the Trivy table output or SARIF file.

# AVD-AWS-0132: "Ensure S3 bucket has versioning enabled"
# The code deployment bucket uses source_hash-based uploads (immutable objects)
# rather than versioning. Versioning would multiply storage costs for large ZIPs.
AVD-AWS-0132

# AVD-AWS-0089: "Ensure S3 bucket logging is enabled"
# Deployment artifact bucket — CloudTrail covers API-level access auditing.
AVD-AWS-0089

# AVD-AWS-0172: "S3 bucket should have lifecycle policies"
# Code bucket uses force_destroy on terraform destroy; S3 lifecycle not needed.
AVD-AWS-0172

# null_resource / local-exec: Trivy may flag shell injection risk on
# local-exec provisioners. These are intentional CLI workarounds for
# resources not supported by the provider (gateway targets, policy engine).
# If Trivy adds a rule for this, add the AVD ID here.
